# REST Controller

## Controller Structure
```java
@RestController
@Tag(name = "ServiceName")
@Validated
@Log4j2
public class MyController {
    private final MyService service;

    public MyController(MyService service) {
        this.service = service;
    }
}
```

## Request/Response
- `@Valid @RequestBody` for Jakarta Bean Validation
- `@Parameter` + `@Schema` for query params
- `201 CREATED` + `Location` header for POST, `204 NO_CONTENT` for DELETE
- `MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE` for produces/consumes

## Error Handling
See `java-conventions.mdc` — controllers throw `ResponseStatusException`, centralized handler converts to RFC 7807.

## OpenAPI & Metrics
- SpringDoc OpenAPI — `@Tag`, `@Operation`, `@ApiResponse`
- OpenTelemetry counters for request metrics
